signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"},{"content_hash":"be9aa7fde63c1d257495af0c7f145f2dc2b1c897e8171069f8c0a7f91dd08627","event_uuid":"131cc858-fecc-4bf3-9734-e79d1a229990","position":{"commit_sha":"fdb212634f3270cf0b87efda6a0e8909dcae4fbb","position":"1784746258363821001-131cc858-fecc-4bf3-9734-e79d1a229990"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"},{"content_hash":"997ae89d425e0e3c785b76e063684c982f30b35b226c83679deabe1584813418","event_uuid":"761b5905-e990-4506-8478-e6b01653e766","position":{"commit_sha":"d133d1ec2c0271c957fb3bf97b1b029e966c2299","position":"1784754560650572001-761b5905-e990-4506-8478-e6b01653e766"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"},{"content_hash":"6795f6e3a48ca2e22278cc3cbb534c84354e0643d93a862b271b397ac3af02f4","event_uuid":"176f38ef-ca32-46af-810f-28364cf717b4","position":{"commit_sha":"d133d1ec2c0271c957fb3bf97b1b029e966c2299","position":"1784754560968525001-176f38ef-ca32-46af-810f-28364cf717b4"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"},{"content_hash":"1e22f4970fed573394426c314aefa603349db6fbc2989ed3d2d0f379452f1349","event_uuid":"02e3ab10-fe73-4589-8a1f-a2f5c8fdc84f","position":{"commit_sha":"e7029295edd2390a4c343b9c16252f878416ad8d","position":"1784754916246454417-02e3ab10-fe73-4589-8a1f-a2f5c8fdc84f"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"}],"bridge_alerts":[],"claim_harness":"claude-code_2-1-217_agent","claim_remote_session":null,"claimed_session":"b3ee85f1-444b-4969-9577-fe7b5a242d7d","comments":[],"created_at":1784695332421070001,"creation_channel":"cli","deps":[],"description":"## Context / Problem\n\nADR 0035 §(d) (\"Adding a second backend\") was only a prose sketch, so the concrete backend\ninterface for Phase 2 (epic `bbf1-82e1-cf9d-494a`) was unspecified. That blocks decomposition\nand plan-review of the implementation stories (S2–S5), which must cite concrete Protocol\nnames. This story lands the §(d) revision that pins the interface.\n\nEdit-set (docs only): `docs/adr/0035-reconciler-vendor-adapter-seam.md`.\n\n## Approach\n\nRewrite §(d) to pin four decisions, each grounded in the current coupling:\n\n- **rebar's local ticket is the canonical model** — no separate `CanonicalTicket`. The seam\n  speaks local-field vocabulary; adapters translate vendor⇄local via the mappers that already\n  exist (`outbound_fields.py`, `inbound_fields.py`/`inbound_translate.py`). No parallel schema\n  kept in lock-step, no redundant `rebar⇄canonical` hop.\n- **Core owns diff/apply; adapters only read + enact.**\n- **Role Protocols behind one `Backend` facade** — `TicketTransport`, `OutboundMapper`,\n  `InboundMapper`, `FieldSanitizer`, `IdentityConvention`, plus opt-in capability Protocols\n  (`SupportsLinks`, `SupportsComments`, `SupportsIncremental`).\n- **One new type `RemoteRef{vendor, instance, remote_id}`** (identity tuple), replacing the\n  hardcoded `\"jira\"` literal in `apply_inbound_records.py` and the bare `jira_key`.\n\nAlso update the Status line, Decision points 5–6, and Consequences to reference the pinned\ndesign and scope the first real second backend to epic `be74-7832-03a8-48ac`.\n\n## Scope\n\n- Revised §(d): the role-Protocol table, the `Backend` facade, `RemoteRef`, the registry\n  keyed on `config.reconciler.backend`, the three leak-fixes, and the proof-of-seam\n  (contract suite + test-only `FakeBackend`; the real GitHub adapter deferred to epic\n  `be74`).\n- Status/Decision/Consequences edits for consistency.\n- No code changes.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] §(d) names all five role Protocols, the `Backend` facade, `RemoteRef`, and the registry\n  keyed on `config.reconciler.backend` — verified by reading the rendered section.\n- [ ] The ADR states the canonical model is rebar's own ticket (no separate model) and lists\n  the three leak-fixes (ADF-sizing out of the differ, lossy-status/parent rules into the Jira\n  adapter, duplicated value-maps/link-constants single-sourced) — verified by `grep` for those\n  terms in the file.\n- [ ] The Status line references epic `bbf1`; the proof-of-seam scopes the first real second\n  backend to epic `be74` — verified by reading.\n- [ ] `make lint` passes on the branch (docs-only change introduces no lint error).","env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","file_impact":[{"path":"docs/adr/0035-reconciler-vendor-adapter-seam.md","reason":"Rewrite §(d) to pin the backend interface, Status/Decision/Consequences edits"}],"keyring":[],"last_status_env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","managed_refs":[["parent","bbf1-82e1-cf9d-494a"]],"parent_id":"bbf1-82e1-cf9d-494a","parent_status_uuid":"761b5905-e990-4506-8478-e6b01653e766","plan_review_phase":"execution","preconditions_summary":{"status":"pre-manifest"},"priority":2,"reverts":[],"status":"in_progress","tags":["reconciler","vendor-adapter","adr"],"ticket_id":"ef33-eaf6-a545-4bfb","ticket_type":"story","title":"ADR 0035 §(d): pin the reconciler backend interface (Protocols + RemoteRef, rebar-model canonical)","verify_commands":[]},"source_event_uuids":["f6b530e9-7330-4d2c-ad8b-8564140dbfc4","e15984ad-66f4-415e-a087-518a84bced51","37823dff-790a-4da8-b240-d95e02042349","4ff25ab0-b594-4a2a-86ca-45e8630c0f36","896e97d7-7255-49cb-981b-9d36ec0c5498","131cc858-fecc-4bf3-9734-e79d1a229990","761b5905-e990-4506-8478-e6b01653e766","176f38ef-ca32-46af-810f-28364cf717b4","02e3ab10-fe73-4589-8a1f-a2f5c8fdc84f"]},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"SNAPSHOT","timestamp":1784754916246454418,"uuid":"9193a024-9b5c-4882-a582-93186d0f7ca1"}